Custom Question 1: Briefly describe how the data will be used
Custom Answer 1: We are undertaking a non-commercial research in support of CARE's 'gender in emergencies' advocacy work. We are conducting big data research into the impacts of disasters on women, and hope to use the dataset to analyse the relationship between the agricultural sector and the likelihood of women and children to survive a disaster and its aftermath. We are being supported to undertake the data analysis in this project pro-bono (for free, and without commercial benefit) by two commercial entities (the Commonwealth Bank of Australia and Quantum Black).
